        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that belongeth to B",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The depression through which the Jordan flows begins to open out at the S.W. foot of Hermon; this seems to be ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the valley",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " alluded to. If, as is probable, Laish-Dan occupied the site of Tell el-Ḳâḍi, Beth-rehob may be identified with Bânias. According to ",
